'''''Bukowski''''' is an upcoming American [[biographical film]]. It retells the early years of writer [[Charles Bukowski]]. The film is to be directed by [[James Franco]] and stars [[Josh Peck]] as Charles Bukowski, [[Tim Blake Nelson]] as his father, Henry, and [[Alex Kingston]] as his mother, Katharina.

== Plot ==
The film focuses on Charles Bukowski's early years: his abusive father, disfiguring acne, alcoholism, and his escape through writing.<ref name=variety>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2013/film/news/keegan-allen-joins-franco-s-bukowski-1118065564/|title=Keegan Allen joins Franco’s ‘Bukowski’|last=McNary|first=Dave|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|date=2013-02-01|accessdate=2014-04-29}}</ref>

== Cast ==
* [[Josh Peck]] as [[Charles Bukowski]], Hank's brother and Henry and Katherina's son
* Jacob Loeb as Hank Bukowski,<ref name=variety/> Charles's brother and Henry and Katherina's son
** Jake Elliott as Hank Bukowski (12-13 years old)
** Jadon Sand as 6 year old Hank Bukowski
* [[Tim Blake Nelson]] as Henry Bukowski,<ref name=variety/> Charles and Hank's father and Katherina's husband
* [[Alex Kingston]] as Katherina Bukowski, Charles and Hank's mother and Henry's wife
** [[Shannen Doherty]] as young Katherina Bukowski<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sbs.com.au/movies/blog/2014/02/04/casting-aspersions-robert-carlyle-becomes-barney-barber|title=Casting Aspersions: Robert Carlyle becomes Barney the barber|last=Mathieson|first=Craig|work=[[Special Broadcasting Service]]|date=2014-02-04|accessdate=2014-04-29}}</ref>
