== Production ==
Shooting began on January 22, 2013, in Los Angeles.<ref name=variety/>  After shooting for two weeks, the crew took a break, with a planned resumption in March 2013.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2013/feb/13/business/la-fi-ct-onlocation-bukowski20130213|title='Bukowski' plays role in modest rise for local film production|last=Verrier|first=Richard|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=2014-02-13|accessdate=2014-04-29}}</ref>  In April 2014, Cyril Humphris announced that he had filed a lawsuit against Franco that alleges that Franco had adapted ''[[Ham on Rye]]'' without the necessary film rights.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/thr-esq/james-franco-sued-violating-film-699013|title=James Franco Sued for Violating Film Rights to Charles Bukowski Novel|last=Gardner|first=Eriq|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=2014-04-25|accessdate=2014-04-29}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://popwatch.ew.com/2014/04/25/james-franco-lawsuit/|title=James Franco sued for violating film rights with Bukowski movie|last=Perlman|first=Jake|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|date=2014-04-25|accessdate=2014-04-29}}</ref> The suit was later dropped.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/thr-esq/james-franco-settles-lawsuit-charles-745235|title=James Franco Settles Lawsuit Over Charles Bukowski Biopic|last=Gardner|first=Eriq|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|date=2014-10-30|accessdate=2015-11-03}}</ref>

== Release ==
''Bukowski'' was planned for release in 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2014/mar/08/entertainment/la-et-jc-bukowski-20140308|title=Moving beyond the Charles Bukowski American lowlife cliche|last=Penner|first=John|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=2013-03-08|accessdate=2014-04-29}}</ref> However, no news has emerged since.

